<p>
   London, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Here are the latest stories from
Bloomberg News at this hour.
<p>
   EU-BA-AMERICAN (Brussels) -- The European Commission raised the
specter of court fights across Europe if the U.K. government
approves the planned alliance of British Airways Plc and American
Airlines over European antitrust objections.
<p>
   EU-ITALY (Brussels) -- The European Commission accused the
Italian government of unnecessarily delaying the opening of its
telecommunications industry, and said the delay raised questions
about the ``credibility'' of the government.
<p>
   LAZARD (London) -- The Lazard houses were the most successful
advisers to cross-border mergers in Europe last year in a business
increasingly dominated by U.S. investment banks, Acquisitions
Monthly magazine said.
<p>
   KOOR (Tel Aviv) -- Koor Industries Ltd., an Israeli holding
company, said Egypt's Kato Industries plans to acquire this month a
``substantial'' holding in it as an economic and political signal.
<p>
   YUGOLAVIA-DEBT (London) -- Cargill Financial Services
International Inc., the financial services unit of Cargill Inc.,
recommended investors reject a rescheduling proposal for $80.4
million of defaulted debt issued by the former Yugoslavia put
forward by Slovenia, Croatia and Macedonia.
