 &UR; BC-EARNS-BANCO-GANADERO-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; BANCO GANADERO SAYS 1996 NET RISES 6.1%, PLANS HIGHER DIVIDEND &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By David Scanlan &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Bogota, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Banco Ganadero, Colombia's
largest bank, said 1996 net income rose 6.1 percent to 56.49
billion pesos ($56.5 million), from 53.24 billion pesos in 1995.
<p>
   The bank also said it will propose a 14 peso per-share annual
dividend, paid out quarterly to common and preferred shareholders,
at its annual meeting March 6. This dividend is an increase of 22
percent over the previous year, the bank said in a statement.
<p>
   Dividend payments will total 43.09 billion pesos.
<p>
   Full quarterly and year-end financial results are to be released
Jan. 29.
<p>
   In addition, Banco Ganadero said it plans to open 50 new
branches in Bogota this year.
</TEXT>
