<TEXT>
<p>
   New York, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Deutsche Morgan Grenfell, the
investment banking arm of Deutsche Bank AG, said it hired three
officials from Goldman Sachs &AMP; Co. in its commercial mortgage and
real estate capital markets units.
<p>
   Mike Offit joins DMG as a director with responsibility for all
commercial and real estate transactions. At Goldman, Offit traded
commercial mortgage-backed securities.
<p>
   Steve Stuart also joins as director, to help expand DMG's role
in worldwide real estate capital markets. Stuart was a vice
president in Goldman's real estate unit.
<p>
   Roger Wittlin will serve as director of DMG's San Francisco
office, helping to establish its fixed-income sales department.
<p>
   DMG will likely hire more officials to its mortgage trading and
mortgage finance units in the coming months, said company
spokewoman Christiana Allaire.
<p>
   In September, DMG hired Kevin Ingram from Goldman to head its
mortgage-backed securities unit.
</TEXT>
