 &UR; BC-TRAVELERS-BUYBACK-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; TRAVELERS RISES TO RECORD ON BUY-BACK, DIVIDEND INCREASE PLANS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Ted Hampton &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   New York, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Travelers Group Inc.'s board
said it would buy back as much as $1 billion of stock and pay an
additional 33 percent on its quarterly dividend, sending the
insurance and financial services company's shares to an all-time
high.
<p>
   Travelers stock rose 2 1/8 to a record 53 3/8 on trading of 1
million shares, approaching its six-month daily trading average of
1.3 million shares by mid-day.
<p>
   The buy-back represents as much as 18.7 million shares, or about
3 percent of 639 million shares outstanding. Repurchases will help
meet demands of Travelers' employee stock option and other benefit
programs, the company said.
<p>
   The company's board voted to pay a 15 cent-a-share quarterly
dividend, up from 11.25 cents. It is payable Feb. 21 to
shareholders of record Feb. 3.
</TEXT>
