 &UR; BC-BBA-ORIOLES-KAMIENECKI-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; ORIOLES SIGN PITCHER SCOTT KAMIENECKI TO MINOR LEAGUE CONTRACT &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Bob Bensch &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Baltimore, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- The Baltimore Orioles signed
pitcher Scott Kamienecki to a minor league contract and invited him
to spring training.
<p>
   Kamienecki, 32, spent his entire six-year major league career
with the New York Yankees. He was 1-2 with an 11.12 earned run
average last season.
<p>
   The right-hander began the season on the disabled list
recovering from surgery to remove bone chips in his pitching elbow.
<p>
   He's coming off a strong performance with Aragua in the
Venezuelan Winter League, going 4-2 with a 1.46 ERA in six starts.
He struck out 33 hitter in 37 innings.
<p>
   Over his six year-career in New York, Kamienecki was 36-39 with
a 4.33 ERA in 113 games.
</TEXT>
