 &UR; BC-EARNS-USAIR-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; USAIR GROUP FOURTH-QUARTER PROFIT FALLS 55% ON HIGHER COSTS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Greg Groeller &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Arlington, Virginia, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- USAir Group Inc.
said its fourth-quarter profit declined 55 percent as the airline
continued to struggle with rising costs.
<p>
   Net income fell to $27.2 million, or 8 cents a share, from $60.3
million, or 61 cents, in the year-earlier quarter. Results are
after payment of preferred dividends.
<p>
   The Arlington, Virginia-based airline's earnings were well-below
analysts expectations of 16 cents a share, based on the average
estimate of 12 analysts surveyed by IBES Inc.
<p>
   Shares of USAir fell 5/8 to 23 1/2 in early afternoon trading.
<p>
   Revenue rose to $2.05 billion from $1.85 billion
<p>
   USAir also said it will pay $50 million in dividends that it
owes to holders of its senior preferred stock.
<p>
   USAir suspended all dividend payments in 1990. Under accounting
practices, however, it must report earnings as if it were still
paying dividends.
<p>
   In the fourth quarter, USAir's total operating expenses rose to
$2 billion from $1.75 billion in the fourth quarter of 1995.
</TEXT>
