<p>
   SPAIN-AUTONOMY (Elche, Spain)  &MD;  The Lady of Elche is Spain's
most famous ancient icon, with its finely chiselled face framed
with an elaborate headdress and necklaces. It represents an Iberian
priestess or princess and is believed to be some 2,500 years old.
When the town of Elche was refused permission to borrow the statue
from Madrid for an anniversary celebration, the dispute became
another skirmish in the perennial tug-of-war over regional
autonomy. A Foreign Journal by Marlise Simons.
