<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-VIACOM-BLOCKBUSTER-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; VIACOM'S BLOCKBUSTER BEGINS BUILDING NEW DISTRIBUTION CENTER &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Karen Fessler &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Fort Lauderdale, Florida, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Viacom Inc.'s
Blockbuster Entertainment unit said it began construction on a
Texas distribution center for its video, music and other products
in North America.
<p>
   The 800,000-square-foot center will be built on 65 acres about
25 miles northeast of Dallas, where Blockbuster is moving its
headquarters from Fort Lauderdale, Florida. The company expects the
center to open in the fall and employ 800 people.
<p>
   Blockbuster currently distributes its products to more than
4,000 stores in the United States and Canada from two centers in
Garland and Dallas, Texas. Blockbuster said it offered employment
at the new center to workers at its two distribution centers.
<p>
   Blockbuster plans to open 700 additional domestic stores this
year. The company earlier this month said it will close 50
Blockbuster Music stores because of sluggish sales.
</TEXT>
