<p>
    &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR; 
<p>
   DIPLOMAT-QUITS (Washington)  &MD;  The highest-ranking US diplomatic
official in Taiwan resigns amid investigation of a possible role in
soliciting Democratic campaign contributions from Taiwanese
businessmen. By Brian McGrory. (w and i coding)
<p>
   DEMS-FUND-RAISING (Washington) -- The appointment of champion
fund-raiser Steve Grossman to run the Democratic National Committee
is a strong indicator that the party's emphasis on filling coffers
is not changing. By Bob Hohler. 1100 words.
<p>
    &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR; 
<p>
   OLIPHANT-COLUMN (Washington) -- In one of the hundreds of
documents made public in Newt Gingrich's ethics case, one stands
out for both its probative and personal value. By Thomas Oliphant.
(w and k coding)
<p>
   NOLAN-COLUMN (Oakland, Calif.) -- When Super Bowl fever sweeps a
city, the party is grand, but the hangover can be massive. By
