 &UR; BC-TRAVELERS-BUYBACK-UPDATE1-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; TRAVELERS RISES TO RECORD ON BUYBACK, DIVIDEND PLANS (UPDATE1) &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Ted Hampton &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
   (Updates share price; adds comment from Travelers official in
third paragraph.)
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   New York, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Travelers Group Inc. said it
would buy back as much as $1 billion of stock and increase its
dividend 33 percent, sending the insurance and financial services
company's shares to an all-time high.
<p>
   Travelers stock rose 2 1/4, or 4.4 percent, to a record 53 1/2
in trading of 1.9 million shares, exceeding its recent daily
trading average of 1.3 million shares by midday.
<p>
   ``The board feels confident about the future,'' said Jeffrey
Lane, vice chairman of Travelers. ``We are generating enormous
amounts of cash flow.'' Z]4 The buyback represents as much as 18.7
million shares at today's price, or about 3 percent of the 639
million shares outstanding. Repurchases will meet demands of
Travelers' employee stock option and other benefit programs, the
company said.
<p>
   Travelers' board voted to increase the company's quarterly
dividend to 15 cents-a-share from 11.25 cents. It's payable on Feb.
21 to investors who held the shares on Feb. 3.
</TEXT>
