<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-TRINIDAD-GLANCE-COX  &QL; 
 &UR; TRINIDAD AND TOBAGO AT-A-GLANCE
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
    &UR; With TRINIDAD-RACE; for release weekend of Jan. 25-26
<p>
    &UR; c.1997 Cox News Service &LR; 
<p>
   Official Name: Republic of Trinidad and Tobago
<p>
   Area: 1,980 square miles (about 1.5 times the size of Rhode
Island)
<p>
   Population: 1.5 million.
<p>
   Ethnic groups: African 40 percent, East Indian 40 percent, mixed
18 percent, European 1 percent, Chinese and other 1 percent.
<p>
   Religions: Roman Catholic 30 percent, Hindu 24 percent, Anglican
11 percent, Muslim 6 percent, Presbyterian 3 percent, other 26
percent.
<p>
   Language: English
<p>
   Government: Parliamentary democracy
<p>
   Gross Domestic Product: $5.2 billion
<p>
   Per capita income: $4,124
<p>
    &UR; Source: U.S. Department of State &LR; 
</TEXT>
