<SLUG> BC-HKN-GRIER-SUPER-BOWL- </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0307 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-HKN-GRIER-SUPER-BOWL-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; EDMONTON OILERS' MIKE GRIER HAS SPECIAL INTEREST IN SUPER BOWL &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Michael Buteau &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Edmonton, Alberta, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Like most of his
teammates, Edmonton Oilers rookie right wing Mike Grier will be
watching the Super Bowl on Sunday.
<p>
   Unlike his teammates, Grier has a personal interest in the game
between the New England Patriots and Green Bay Packers. His father,
Bobby Grier, is the Patriots' director of player personnel.
<p>
   ``It's kind of an emotional game for me,'' said Grier, who grew
up in Holliston, Massachusetts, and has been a Patriots fan his
whole life. ``Hopefully they can win.''
<p>
   Before he can turn his mind to football though, Grier will have
to focus on his team's hockey game against the Capitals in
Washington.
<p>
   ``Luckily our game is in the afternoon (noon Washington time),''
Grier said, ``so I'll have plenty of time to watch the Super
Bowl.''
<p>
   The Super Bowl starts about six hours later in New Orleans.
<p>
   The 22-year-old Grier, who at 6-foot-1, 235 pounds could almost
pass for an NFL linebacker, said his choice of hockey over football
was geographically influenced.
<p>
   ``I basically grew up my whole life in Massachusetts and it's a
pretty big hockey area,'' he said. ``Once I got into it and started
playing, I really fell in love with it.''
<p>
   Grier's father was the Patriots running backs coach in 1985 when
the Chicago Bears trounced New England 46-10 in Super Bowl XX.
<p>
   His son, who won a national championship with Boston University
in 1995, hopes Dad has better luck the second time around.
<p>
   ``In '85 things didn't go so well,'' said Grier, who has five
goals and nine assists in 45 games with Edmonton this season. ``I'm
just glad he has another shot at it.''
</TEXT>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-22-97 1443EST
</TRAILER>
