<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-BKN-ALL-STAR-VOTING-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; BARKLEY CONTINUES TO LEAD WESTERN CONFERENCE ALL-STAR VOTING &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Pete Coates &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   New York, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Houston Rockets forward Charles
Barkley continues to lead all Western Conference players after five
weeks of balloting for the NBA All-Star Game.
<p>
   Barkley, who has played in the last nine All-Star Games, has
received 1,413,480 votes, 84,086 more than Seattle forward Shawn
Kemp.
<p>
   Trailing Barkley and Kemp among Western Conference forwards are
Utah's Karl Malone with 980,882 votes and Minnesota's Kevin Garnett
with 374,314. Among guards, Seattle's Gary Payton and Utah's John
Stockton remain the leaders with 932,465 and 904,531 votes,
respectively, ahead of Phoenix's Jason Kidd with 671,610 and
Houston's Clyde Drexler with 663,502.
<p>
   Barkley's teammate Hakeem Olajuwon has received 1,156,532 votes,
maintaining a 141,269-vote lead over the Los Angeles Lakers'
Shaquille O'Neal at center. They are followed by San Antonio's
David Robinson with 541,199 votes and Seattle's Sam Perkins with
139,570.
<p>
   The All-Star Game will be played at Gund Arena in Cleveland on
Sunday, Feb. 9. The starters will be announce Sunday, with reserves
named next week.
</TEXT>
