<SLUG> BC-BRAZIL-STOCKS-CLOSE-B </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0304 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-BRAZIL-STOCKS-CLOSE-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; BRAZIL STOCKS FALL AMID CONCERN STATE COMPANIES ARE EXPENSIVE &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Sao Paulo, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Brazilian stocks fell because
of concern that state-controlled companies like Telecomunicacoes
Brasilieras SA, Petroleo Brasileiro SA and Centrais Eletricas
Brasileiras SA are more expensive than their earnings prospects
justify.
<p>
   ``I'm surprised the fall isn't harder. I wouldn't buy these
stocks at these prices,'' said Sergio Blatyta, chief trader at
Banco Votorantim SA.
<p>
   The Bovespa index for the Sao Paulo stock exchange fell 874
points, or 1.1 percent, to 78,175.01, only the third decline so far
this year. In Rio de Janeiro, the IBV index fell 168 points, or 0.6
percent, to 29,581.
<p>
   The federally controlled telephone company known as Telebras and
the federal utility called Eletrobras rose to all-time highs
yesterday.
<p>
   The companies led a rally that pushed the Bovespa index 12.3
percent higher before today's decline. The companies account for 69
percent of the weight exchange officials assign to the index.
<p>
   Telebras, Petrobras and Eletrobras rose on government plans to
sell state assets this year and to open the oil and
telecommunications industries to private investment.
--Herbert Lash in Sao Paulo at (5511) 3048-4532 through the New
York newsroom (212) 318-2300/cp
Story illustration: To graph the performance of Sao Paulo stock
exchange, see IBOV Index &QR;  GP.
For stock market news: Regional news: NI STK Stocks NI LATAM Latin
American NI BZS Brazil Stocks NI BRAZIL Brazil
For emerging markets news: NI EM Emerging Markets
For top Brazilian news: TNI BRAZIL TOP.
