<SLUG> BC-QUICK-&AMP;-REILLY-UPDATE </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0297 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-QUICK-&AMP;-REILLY-UPDATE1-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; QUICK &AMP; REILLY AGREE TO BUY SPECIALIST NASH WEISS (UPDATE1) &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Jon Friedman &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
   (Adds quotes from Quick &AMP; Reilly President Thomas Quick.
Rewrites. Updates stock quote.)
Palm Beach, Florida, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Quick &AMP; Reilly Group
Inc. said it agreed to acquire Nash, Weiss &AMP; Co., a Nasdaq market
maker. Terms weren't disclosed.
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Thomas Quick, president of Quick &AMP; Reilly, said the proposed
acquisition wouldn't hurt his firm's earnings. ``This will give us
returns that the shareholders are used to,'' Quick said.
<p>
   Quick &AMP; Reilly said Dec. 18 that earnings rose 22 percent in the
third quarter ended Nov. 29 from the comparable year-earlier
period.
<p>
   Nash Weiss would contribute $60 million in annual revenue to
Quick &AMP; Reilly, which had revenue of $500 million last year. No
acquisition in Quick &AMP; Reilly history has produced a revenue gain
of that amount, Quick said.
<p>
   Quick said he expected the transaction to be completed by Feb.
28.
<p>
   ``We have been selective in making acquisitions,'' Quick said.
He said Nash Weiss will remain under its current management and
remain at its Jersey City, New Jersey, headquarters.
<p>
   Nash Weiss is the fifth-largest independently owned Nasdaq
trading firm, executing orders in about 2,500 issues a day, Quick
said.
<p>
   Quick &AMP; Reilly's shares were unchanged at 33 1/8 in late
afternoon trading.
<p>
   For Nash Weiss, Quick &AMP; Reilly's financial strength will help
the firm increase the number of stocks in which it makes a market,
Ronald Weiss, chairman of Nash Weiss, said in a statement.
<p>
   Quick &AMP; Reilly operates the nation's third-largest discount
brokerage firm and has a securities clearing subsidiary.
</TEXT>
