<STORYID cat=d pri=r sel=ttx-z> A9098 </STORYID>
<SLUG> BC-SOFTDRINK-FOODS-TEX </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0510 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
BC-SOFTDRINK-FOODS-TEX &QL; 
SODA 'LICIOUS: YOU'LL BE SURPRISED WHAT POPS UP IN THESE RECIPES &QL; 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) &QL; 
By BEVERLY BUNDY &QC; 
c.1997 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   We don't just drink them; we also eat soft drinks. The sugar
component in carbonated drinks makes it a versatile ingredient in
the kitchen. The following recipes are from ``Square Meals'' by
Jane and Michael Stern (Knopf, $21.95). 
<p>
   DR PEPPER BAKED BEANS
<p>
   Serves 4-6
<p>
   28-ounce can pork and beans
<p>
   1 onion, chopped fine
<p>
   1 green bell pepper, chopped fine
<p>
   1 tomato, chopped fine
<p>
   1/2 cup dark brown sugar
<p>
   1/3 cup Dr Pepper
<p>
   1/8 teaspoon ground cloves
<p>
   Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
<p>
   Drain liquid from pork and beans. Pour into baking dish. Gently
mix in vegetables. Combine sugar, Dr Pepper and cloves until sugar
is dissolved. Pour evenly over bean mixture. Bake covered for 30
minutes.
<p>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 221 calories, 2 grams fat, 47
grams carbohydrates, 9 grams protein, 8 milligrams cholesterol, 501
milligrams sodium, 6 percent of calories from fat. 
<p>
   PEPSI-COLA CAKE WITH BROILED PEANUT BUTTER FROSTING
<p>
   Serves 12-14
<p>
   Cake:
<p>
   2 cups all-purpose flour
<p>
   2 cups sugar
<p>
   1/2 pound butter
<p>
   2 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa
<p>
   1 cup Pepsi
<p>
   1/2 cup buttermilk
<p>
   2 eggs, beaten
<p>
   1 teaspoon baking soda
<p>
   1 teaspoon vanilla extract
<p>
   1 1/2 cups miniature marshmallows
<p>
   Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease and flour 9-by-13-by-2-inch
pan.
<p>
   Combine flour and sugar in large bowl. Melt butter, add cocoa
and Pepsi. Pour over flour and sugar mixture and stir until
well-blended. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla. Mix well.
Stir in marshmallows. Pour into pan.
<p>
   Bake 40 minutes. Remove cake from oven and frost while still
warm.
<p>
   Frosting:
<p>
   6 tablespoons butter
<p>
   1 cup packed dark brown sugar
<p>
   2/3 cup peanut butter
<p>
   1/4 cup milk
<p>
   2/3 cup chopped peanuts
<p>
   Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter. Add milk and stir well.
Add nuts. Spread over warm cake. Place frosted cake under broiler
about 4 inches from heat source. Broil just a few seconds or until
topping starts to bubble. Be careful not to scorch.
<p>
   Let cool at least 30 minutes before serving.
<p>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 543 calories, 29 grams fat, 68
grams carbohydrates, 8 grams protein, 81 milligrams cholesterol,
275 milligrams sodium, 48 percent of calories from fat. 
<p>
   JOEL'S BEST JELL-O
<p>
   Serves 6-8
<p>
   3-ounce package Jell-O, any flavor
<p>
   1 cup boiling water
<p>
   8 ounces cold cola
<p>
   8-ounce package cream cheese, cut into 1/2-inch cubes
<p>
   1 cup drained, pitted dark cherries
<p>
   1/2 cup nuts, if desired
<p>
   Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. When cooled to room
temperature, add cola, cream cheese, cherries and nuts. Pour into
oiled 6-cup mold. Chill until set. Unmold to serve.
<p>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 215 calories, 15 grams fat, 16
grams carbohydrates, 7 grams protein, 31 milligrams cholesterol,
103 milligrams sodium, 62 percent of calories from fat.
</TEXT>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-22-97 1523EST
</TRAILER>
