<SLUG> BC-HKN-PENGUINS-LEMIEUX- </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0160 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-HKN-PENGUINS-LEMIEUX-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; PENGUINS' MARIO LEMIEUX LISTED AS DAY-TO-DAY WITH BACK SPASMS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Michael Buteau &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Pittsburgh, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Pittsburgh Penguins center
Mario Lemieux is listed as day-to-day after leaving last night's
game with back spasms.
<p>
   Lemieux was injured when he crashed into the net after getting
tangled up with Calgary Flames defenseman Steve Chiasson late in
the first period of Pittsburgh's 4-2 win.
<p>
   Before leaving the game, Lemieux, the National Hockey League's
leading scorer with 80 points, scored his 30th goal of the season.
<p>
   A five time Art Ross Trophy winner as the NHL's scoring
champion, Lemieux has a 15-game point-scoring streak heading into
tomorrow's game against the Colorado Avalanche.
<p>
   Lemieux, who has missed only one game this season, missed the
entire 1994-95 season due to back problems and Hodgkin's disease.
</TEXT>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-22-97 1550EST
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
