</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Dallas, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Major League Soccer's Dallas Burn
signed Argentine First Division player Daniel Peinado, filling the
team's defensive midfielder role.
<p>
   Terms of the contract weren't disclosed.
<p>
   Peinado, 29, joins the Burn after spending the last five months
with America de Cali in the Colombian First Division, where he was
on loan from Lanus of the Argentine First Division. rBN-;B A
veteran of 10 years of professional soccer in Argentinfsq0Peinado
has scored 20 goals during his career.
<p>
   ``Daniel is the type of guy that is willing to do the dirty work
for his team,'' said Carlos Cordoba, a Burn assistant coach. ``He
stops the opposition's attack and starts the offensive with his
excellent ball distribution.''
<p>
   Before joining America de Cali, Peinado played for Lanus from
1993-96 after spending seven seasons with Estudiantes de La Plata
of the Argentine First Division.
<p>
   With America de Cali, Peinado played with midfielder Carlos
Valderama of MLS's Tampa Bay Mutiny.
</TEXT>
