<SLUG> BC-ULTRACAFFEINE-TASTETE </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0383 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
BC-ULTRACAFFEINE-TASTETEST-TEX &QL; 
BOY SCOUTS WAY IN ON NEW OFFERINGS BY COKE AND PEPSI &QL; 
EDS: Accompanied by ULTRA CAFFEINE-DRINKS and ULTRA CAFFEINE-BOX. &QL; 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) &QL; 
By BEVERLY BUNDY &QC; 
c.1997 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   We asked Boy Scout Troop No. 7 in Grapevine, Texas, to
taste-test the new Surge and Josta sodas. In retrospect, this may
not have been the wisest idea.
<p>
   ``We limit the boys to one to two cans of soda on a campout,''
Scoutmaster Dave Creeger said. ``Once we brought a whole truck-load
of sodas and they got so wired, we couldn't control them. So now we
drink a lot of Gatorade.''
<p>
   Here's what the Scouts said: 
<p>
   Surge
<p>
   Made by: Coca-Cola
<p>
   Secret ingredient: Maltodextrin, the carbohydrate in PowerAde
<p>
   Caffeine: 52 milligrams
<p>
   Sugar: 42 grams
<p>
   Comments:
<p>
   ``It reminds me of Gatorade, but it doesn't have an aftertaste.
I don't think a cola drinker would want something like Gatorade.''
 &MD;  Michael Cohen, 12.
<p>
   ``It tastes like a combination of Sprite and Mountain Dew.''  &MD; 
Ryan Akins, 15.
<p>
   ``I like the twang to it.''  &MD;  Matthew Boyle, 14.
<p>
   ``I like the bright color.''  &MD;  Spencer Waller, 12.
<p>
   ``It has a sour taste, but it's likable.''  &MD;  Ross Ponder, 12.
<p>
   ``I like the citrus taste and the green color.''  &MD;  Chris
McNosky, 11.
<p>
   ``I've got a boy addicted to Mountain Dew. This does not make my
heart sing.''  &MD;  Dee McNosky, mother of Chris. 
<p>
   Josta
<p>
   Made by: Pepsi
<p>
   Secret ingredient: Guarana berry, a natural stimulant
<p>
   Caffeine: 59 milligrams
<p>
   Sugar: 44 grams
<p>
   Comments:
<p>
   ``I like cream soda, so I like Josta. I like the legend about
primal power.''  &MD;  Brian Lawson, 12.
<p>
   ``It tastes like snow-cone syrup.''  &MD;  Ross Ponder, 12.
<p>
   ``I don't like the flavor and it tastes flat.''  &MD;  Jonathan
Akins, 15.
<p>
   ``It tastes like dull cream soda, but it says it has primal
power and that's good.''  &MD;  Michael Cohen, 12.
<p>
   ``I like Josta better because of the can and it has stuff in it
like cream soda and Big Red. It's better than Surge. I don't like
citrus.''  &MD;  Michael Nahat, 12.
<p>
   ``I liked Josta. It didn't taste like it had more caffeine.''  &MD; 
Brett Carlson, 12.
<p>
   ``It scares me to death. They don't need any more energy than
they already have.''  &MD;  Diane Carlson, mother of Brett.
</TEXT>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-22-97 1605EST
</TRAILER>
