<p>
   FBN-PARCELLS-HOLMGREN (New Orleans) -- Green Bay Packers coach
Mike Holmgren is taking a page from the manual of Phil Jackson, who
frequently uses Zen Buddhist teachings to motivate his NBA champion
Chicago Bulls. By Scott Soshnick.
<p>
   FBN-SWITCHED-SIDES (New Orleans) -- Two players in the Super
Bowl know about life on the other side. Mike Bartrum and Jeff
Dellenbach played for both the Green Bay Packers and the New
England Patriots this season, and will be on opposite sidelines on
Sunday. By Scott Soshnick.
<p>
   HKN-GRIER-SUPER-BOWL (Edmonton, Alberta) -- Like most of his
teammates, Edmonton Oilers rookie right wing Mike Grier will be
watching the Super Bowl on Sunday. Unlike his teammates, Grier has
a personal interest in the game between the New England Patriots
and Green Bay Packers. His father, Bobby Grier, is the Patriots'
director of player personnel. By Michael Buteau.
<p>
   BKC-UCONN-SUSPENSIONS (Storrs, Connecticut) -- The suspension of
University of Connecticut basketball players Ricky Moore and Kirk
King will extend at least through tonight's game against Miami. By
Pete Coates.
<p>
   BBA-ORIOLES-KAMIENECKI (Baltimore) -- The Baltimore Orioles
signed pitcher Scott Kamienecki to a minor league contract and
invited him to spring training. By Bob Bensch.
<p>
   BKN-ALL-STAR-VOTING (New York) -- Houston Rockets forward
Charles Barkley continues to lead all Western Conference players
after five weeks of balloting for the NBA All-Star Game. By Pete
Coates.
<p>
   (END BLOOMBERG NYTNS BUDGET)
