<p>
   ``They have gear that no one else has,'' said Hanley, 27, a
photographer and computer artist who lives in Los Feliz. ``They pay
attention to inks, to archiving and to color. And it's one of the
few places in L.A. that has an Iris printer.''
<p>
   According to Charles Leavitt, the firm's production manager and
artist liaison, the Iris handles the bulk of Muse X's artistic
load. The highly specialized printer sprays watercolor inks through
