<STORYID cat=f pri=r sel=tia-z> A9241 </STORYID>
<SLUG> BC-TEXAS-STOCKS-BLOOM </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0198 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-TEXAS-STOCKS-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &TL; TEXAS STOCKS INDEX FALLS, LED BY CLIFFS DRILLING CO &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
 &TL;  
 &TL;       Houston, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Texas stocks index fell, led by Cliffs
 &TL; Drilling Co and Energy Ventures Inc.
 &TL;       The Bloomberg Texas Stock Index, a price weighted list of companies
 &TL; with operations in the region, fell 1.06 to 163.02.
 &TL;       Cliffs Drilling Co, fell 5 1/64 to 65. Energy Ventures Inc fell 4 1/8
 &TL; to 57 7/8.
 &TL;       In the broader market, the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 Index rose 0.35 to
