<SLUG> BC-BRAZIL-ASSET-SALES-BL </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0393 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-BRAZIL-ASSET-SALES-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; SAO PAULO SIGNS ACCORD WITH BOVESPA TO EASE STATE ASSETS SALES &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Ian McCluskey &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Sao Paulo, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- The Sao Paulo state government
signed an accord with Bovespa, the Sao Paulo stock exchange, for
converting the debts of state-owned companies into securities to
help sell the companies to private investors.
<p>
   The state-owned companies will be sold in a four-stage process
coordinated by Companhia Paulista de Administracao de Ativos (CPA),
a company created by the Sao Paulo state government.
<p>
   CPA's main task is to securitize the debts of state companies,
creating a currency that can be used by investors to acquire shares
of the companies at auction.
<p>
   ``Creditors will be switching debts which are often difficult to
collect for debts that are tied to real assets,'' said Sergio Luis
de Cerqueira, special assistant to the president of Bovespa.
<p>
   In the first stage of the securitization process, shares of
state-own companies are transferred to CPA, which then issues
debentures backed by those shares. Next, debts of state-owned
companies to creditors and suppliers are consolidated by the Sao
Paulo state finance secretary and registered at Bovespa.
<p>
   In the third stage, the companies' creditors may purchase the
debentures issued by CPA, up to the amount they're owed, at
auctions held at Bovespa. Finally, the creditors can use the
debentures to purchase shares of the state-owned companies at
auctions, also be conducted at Bovespa.
<p>
   Bovespa and CPA signed an accord today outlining the
responsibilities of each party in the securitization process.
<p>
   In addition to staging the auctions of debentures and
state-owned company shares, Bovespa will be responsible for the
custody of the debentures issued by CPA.
<p>
   Bovespa also will administer a secondary market for the
debentures. Any investor interested in buying shares of a
state-owned company will be able to purchase the debentures.
<p>
   Shares worth 1.8 billion reais of Companhia Paulista de Forca e
Luz, a Sao Paulo utility, and Companhia de Saneamento Basico do
Estado de Sao Paulo, a water and sewage company, already have been
transferred to CPA.
<p>
   The two state-owned companies will be among the first to be put
up for sale at Bovespa.
</TEXT>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-22-97 1648EST
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
