   Company News
<p>
   FOOD-LION-ABC (Greensboro, North Carolina) -- Food Lion Inc.
wins $5.5 million in punitive damages from Walt Disney Co.'s ABC in
a surprising verdict that could reduce the number of hidden-camera
exposes. By Joseph Menn.
<p>
   FEDERAL-EXPRESS-PRICES (Memphis, Tennessee) -- Federal Express
Corp. said it will adjust its U.S. express delivery prices for
distance and weight, matching last year's move by Atlanta-based
rival United Parcel Service of America Inc. By Kathleen Sullivan.
<p>
   QUICK-NASH (New York)-- Quick &AMP; Reilly Group Inc., the nation's
third-largest discount brokerage firm, said it agreed to acquire
Nasdaq specialist firm Nash, Weiss &AMP; Co. for an undisclosed amount.
By Jon Friedman.
<p>
   AT&AMP;T-CONNECTICUT (New York) -- AT&AMP;T Corp. to begin providing
local phone services in Connecticut in the second week of February,
pitting the nation's largest long-distance company against
incumbent Southern New England Telephone Co.
<p>
   Washington
<p>
   CONGRESS-TAXES (Washington) -- Senate Republicans opened the
1997 debate over how to cut U.S. taxes with a plan that includes
some help for corporate America, including reducing the maximum its
capital gains rates from 35 percent to 28 percent. By Paul Nyhan.
<p>
   FED-GLITCH (Washington) -- The Federal Reserve inadvertently
released its regional survey of economic conditions almost two
hours early today, and officials at the central bank are still
trying to sort out what happened. By Laura Cohn and Vincent Del
Giudice.
<p>
   FAA-COSTS (Washington) The Federal Aviation Administration does
not have a reliable cost estimating process in place to guide air
traffic control improvement decisions, government auditors say, and
the result could be hundreds of millions of dollars spent poorly or
even unnecessarily. By Jennifer Thomas.
<p>
   Latin America
PANAMA-CONFIDENCE (New York) -- Panama received its debut rating,
equivalent to a ``junk'' bond, from both Moody's Investors Service
and Standard &AMP; Poor's Corp. -- vaulting to the top tier of Latin
American nations and signaling growing confidence in the region. By
Jill Hamburg.
