<p>
   TSONGAS-LEGACY (Lowell, Mass.)  &MD;  When Paul Tsongas died last
weekend, the local newspaper here wrote, ``With his death, Paul
Tsongas's survivors include his wife, his children and a city.''
For the rest of the country, the name Paul Tsongas may only conjure
up vague memories of a man who made a quixotic bid for the
presidency. But for the people of Lowell, who have turned out in
the thousands to pay their respects at his house, Paul Tsongas was
a hero whose legacy will not only be the buildings and the arenas
he helped to build, but the memories of the locals who credit him,
more than anything else, with rescuing the city from the depression
that came with the collapse of the old textile factories. By Sara
Rimer.
