<TEXT>
<p>
   Chicago, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- The Chicago Cubs signed
infielders Dave Hansen and Andujar Cedeno to minor league contracts
and invited both to spring training.
<p>
   Hansen, 28, was used mostly as a pinch-hitter with the Los
Angeles Dodgers last season, batting .221 with six runs batted. He
collected 11 hits in 43 pinch-hitting appearances.
<p>
   Originally selected by the Dodgers in the 1986 June Draft,
Hansen has compiled a .259 career batting average with 12 home runs
and 83 RBI.
<p>
   Cedeno, 27, spent last season with the Detroit Tigers, San Diego
Padres and Houston Astros, batting a combined .213 with 10 home
runs and 38 RBI.
<p>
   A six-year major league veteran, Cedeno has compiled a .236
career batting average with 47 home runs and 223 RBI.
