<SLUG> BC-COLORADO-STOCKS-CLOSE </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0254 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-COLORADO-STOCKS-CLOSE2-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; COLORADO INDEX FALLS, LED BY BARRETT RESOURCES (UPDATE1) &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Jeanie Stokes &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
   (Adds detail on Barrett loss.)
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Denver, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Colorado stocks index fell, led
by Barrett Resources Corp. and Newmont Mining Corp.
<p>
   The Bloomberg Colorado Stock Index, a price weighted list of
companies with operations in the region, fell 0.34 to 139.37.
<p>
   Barrett Resources fell 1 5/8 to 40 1/4 along with other oil and
gas stocks as the industry awaited the release of the American
Petroleum Institute's weekly inventory report after the close of
commodity trading. The Standard &AMP; Poor's Smallcap Oil and Gas Index
fell 5.17, or 3.06 percent, to 163.65.
<p>
   February gold contracts fell $2.10 to $351.70 an ounce in
trading on the New York Mercantile Exchange Comex division, and the
declining gold prices continued to depress the state's gold mining
sector.
<p>
   Newmont Mining fell 1 to 39 5/8, while its operating unit,
Newmont Gold Co. fell 3/4 to 39 1/4. Golden Star Resources Ltd.
fell 3/4 to 14. Amax Gold Inc. fell 1/8 to 6 1/8. Echo Bay Mines
Ltd. also fell 1/8 to 6 3/16.
<p>
   In the broader market, the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 Index rose 3.50
to 786.22. The Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 33.87 to 6,850.03.
<p>
   The Colorado Stock Index was developed with a base value of 100
as of Dec. 30, 1994. The state index has advanced 2.21 percent this
year, compared with 6.14 percent for the S&AMP;P 500.
</TEXT>
