NYT-01-22-97 1807EST
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCID> nyt970122.0505 </DOCID>
<STORYID cat=f pri=r sel=tia-z> A9514 </STORYID>
<SLUG> BC-EARNS-MYLAN-LABORATOR </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0260 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-EARNS-MYLAN-LABORATORIES-UPDATE1-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; MYLAN LABORATORIES 3RD-QTR NET FALLS 18% ON COSTS (UPDATE1) &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Marc Monseau &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
   (Adds closing stock price.)
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Pittsburgh, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Mylan Laboratories Inc. said
fiscal third-quarter earnings fell 18 percent, as costs rose and
revenue from its Somerset Pharmaceuticals venture dropped.
<p>
   Mylan's net income dropped to $18.1 million, or 15 cents a
share, in the quarter ended Dec. 31, from $21.9 million, or 18
cents, in the year-earlier quarter.
<p>
   Revenue rose 25 percent to $114 million from $91.3 million.
<p>
   The results were below Wall Street expectations. The generic
drugmaker was expected to earn 18 cents a share, according to the
average estimate of 12 analysts surveyed by IBES International Inc.
<p>
   Mylan shares fell 1/4 to 17 3/4 in trading of 653,800, compared
with a three-month daily average of 490,600.
<p>
   Pittsburgh-based Mylan said its cost of sales rose 40 percent to
$66.7 million from $47.6 million. Selling and administrative
expenses increased 34 percent to $97.1 million from $72.7 million.
<p>
   Revenue from Somerset, a joint venture with Watson
Pharmaceuticals Inc., fell 38 percent to $9.84 million from $16
million. Watson stock climbed 5/8 to 45 3/8.
<p>
   In the latest nine-month period, Mylan made net income of $49.4
million, or 41 cents a share, down from $84.6 million, or 71 cents,
in the year-earlier period.
<p>
   Revenue increased 7.8 percent to $321.5 million from $298.2
million.
</TEXT>
