<SLUG> BC-TEN-DAVIS-CUP-RENEBER </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0195 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-TEN-DAVIS-CUP-RENEBERG-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; RENEBERG NAMED INJURY REPLACEMENT TO U.S. DAVIS CUP TEAM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Bob Bensch &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   White Plains, New York, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Richey Reneberg
has been named as an injury replacement for Todd Martin on the U.S.
Davis Cup team for its 1997 opening round tie in Brazil, Feb. 7-12.
<p>
   Martin has tendinitis in his right knee, which forced him out of
the Australian Open. He had hoped to recover to be able to compete
in Brazil.
<p>
   ``Todd has always made Davis Cup a priority in his scheduling
and has made many great contributions to the team's success in
previous years,'' said U.S. captain Tom Gullikson. ``Richey
Reneberg has always stepped up when called on for Davis Cup play. I
am fortunate to have a player of Richey's ability and Davis Cup
experience to turn to.''
<p>
   Reneberg played Davis Cup from 1993-95 and his record is 4-2 in
doubles and 1-0 in singles. His most recent competition came in
Italy in 1995 when he teamed with Jared Palmer to win the doubles.
He was also a member of the 1995 team that beat Russia in the
final, but didn't play.
</TEXT>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-22-97 1816EST
</TRAILER>
