 &UR; BC-BBA-INDIANS-MULLIGAN-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; INDIANS PURCHASE CONTRACT OF CATCHER SEAN MULLIGAN FROM PADRES &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Dan Bollerman &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Cleveland, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- The Cleveland Indians
purchased the contract of catcher Sean Mulligan from the San Diego
Padres, the team said.
<p>
   Cleveland then designated the 27-year-old for assignment so he
could be sent to one of the Indians' minor-league teams if he
clears waivers. He also will be invited to Cleveland's major-league
spring-training camp as a non-roster player.
<p>
   Mulligan appeared in two games with San Diego in 1996 and was
hitless in his only at-bat.
<p>
   He batted .288 in 103 games with the Padres' Triple-A Las Vegas
affiliate, reaching career highs with 19 home runs and 75 runs
batted in.
<p>
   Mulligan was a fourth-round selection of San Diego in the 1991
amateur draft out of the University of Illinois.
</TEXT>
