laboratory, Edward J.A. Pope wages war on diabetes, one of
mankind's most vexing diseases. Pope's most potent weapon, and one
that he developed, is a ``sol-gel'' process not yet found in
medical facilities. The process, for which he has patents pending,
produces small, pale-pink ceramic beads that encase a collection of
insulin-producing beta cells.
