<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-RJR-SORENSEN-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; R.J. REYNOLDS HEAD OF MARKETING, SORENSEN, LEAVES COMPANY &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Leslie Hillman &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Winston-Salem, North Carolina, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- R.J.
Reynolds Tobacco Co. said its head of marketing Ove Sorensen is
leaving the company after 15 months.
<p>
   Sorensen, 55, joined the U.S. tobacco arm of RJR Nabisco
Holdings Corp. from Guinness Plc's United Distillers unit in
October 1995.
<p>
   The company said he won't be replaced.
<p>
   Reynolds had heralded Sorensen as a savvy marketer, who would
strengthen its brands, which included the aging Winston and Salem
cigarettes. Fifteen months later, while Reynolds has introduced 19
new products, Winston and Salem are still losing market share.
<p>
   RJR shares rose 1/8 to 33 7/8 today. The company made the
announcement of Sorensen's departure after the market closed.
</TEXT>
