<TEXT>
<p>
   New York, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Trump Hotels &AMP; Casino Resorts
Inc. said Colony Capital Inc. will purchase $125 million of
cumulative preferred securities as part of Colony's plan to buy 51
percent of its Trump's Castle casino.
<p>
   Colony Capital, a Los Angeles-based real estate fund, will
receive $62.5 million of cumulative preferred shares and another
$62.5 million of preferred shares convertible into Trump Hotels
stock after the fourth year of the agreement, according to a Trump
Hotels federal filing. Colony can receive a maximum of 8.5 million
Trump Hotels shares under the agreement.
<p>
   Trump announced preliminary terms of the agreement Monday.
<p>
   Both categories of preferred shares have a compound dividend
rate of 15 percent and are due in eight years, the company said in
the filing. Colony will also receive warrants for 2 million Trump
Hotels with a strike price of $15 a share upon completion of the
transaction, the company said.
<p>
   In addition, Trump Hotels said it will ``cancel'' the $58
million of 13 7/8 pay-in-kind notes tied to the Castle.
<p>
   Trump shares fell 1/4 to 11 1/4.
</TEXT>
