<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-FLEET-JOBS-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FLEET TO SHIFT 800 BRANCH JOBS TO INVESTMENTS, OTHER SERVICES &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Alvin Powell &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Boston, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- Fleet Financial Group Inc. said
it will cut 800 jobs from its branches to beef up insurance sales,
investment services and telephone banking operations.
<p>
   Boston-based Fleet, the nation's 11th-largest bank, said
increased demand for non-traditional banking services, particularly
telephone banking, prompted the move.
<p>
   ``We have seen a dramatic increase in customer usage of
telephone banking, in particular, and seen strong increase in
customer demand for products and services beyond the scope of
traditional bank services,'' said Fleet spokesman James Mahoney.
<p>
   Though 800 branch jobs will be lost, less than 800 workers will
be fired, Mahoney said. Some of the bank branch employees will be
offered new jobs in other areas, and some branch positions are
already vacant, he said. Fleet employs about 35,000 workers.
<p>
   Fleet, which operates about 1,200 branches in seven Northeastern
states said its fourth-quarter earnings rose 16 percent to $302
million, as its recent acquisitions and increases in its national
lending business paid off.
<p>
   Fleet shares rose 1 7/8 to 55 in trading of 1.30 million shares,
compared with their three-month daily average of 721,200.
</TEXT>
