<TEXT>
<p>
   Ottawa, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- JDS Fitel Inc.'s shares rose 12
percent after the company said fiscal second-quarter profit almost
tripled on demand for its fiber-optic transmission equipment.
<p>
   The shares of the Ottawa-based company climbed C$3 to C$27.75 in
Toronto trading of 124,108, compared with the three-month daily
average of 42,475.
<p>
   JDS said yesterday that net income rose to C$5.3 million (US$3.9
million), or 22 cents a share, for the period ended Nov. 30, from
C$1.8 million, or nine cents, in the year-earlier period.
<p>
   Revenue jumped 58 percent to C$26.4 million from C$16.7 million.
<p>
   Brian Piccioni, an analyst with Marleau, Lemire Securities Inc.
in Montreal, said JDS Fitel's second-quarter earnings per share
exceeded his forecast of C$0.19.
<p>
   The declining cost of fiber-optic cable, he said, should benefit
JDS Fitel by accelerating the pace of installation.
<p>
   Piccioni rates JDS's stock a ``strong buy'' and has a 12-month
target price of C$31.50.
<p>
   For the six-month period, JDS Fitel's net income rose 83 percent
to C$8.6 million, or 36 cents a share, from C$4.7 million, or 23
cents, in the year-earlier period.
<p>
   Revenue increased 46 percent to C$46.7 million from C$32.1
million.
</TEXT>
