chemical engineering major, is one of Brazil's most successful
singer-songwriters. ``Music was like a hobby,'' recalls Lins, whose
work is among some of the most-recorded of those of any Brazilian
songwriters, particularly among American jazz musicians. Lins'
latest release, ``I'm Not Alone,'' is heavily influenced by his
return to Brazil in its ``bossa nova-like quiet sophistication,''
writes Marty Lipp. By Marty Lipp. From The Beat magazine. 700
words. Moves Wednesday. (slugged:
BC-NU-IVAN-LINS-BRAZILIAN-SONGWRITER-(WORLDMUSIC)-NYTSF)
