<p>
   TECHNOLOGY-WASHINGTON (Seattle) Technology-based industries are
now responsible for 778,000 jobs, or one-third of all employment,
in Washington state, according to a new report prepared by two
University of Washington geographers for the Technology Alliance.
In the study, technology-based companies are those with at least 10
percent of their workforce involved in research and development.
They companies employ nearly 231,000 people directly; each of those
jobs generates 2.37 more in trade, services and other fields, to
reach the 778,000 figure. The study is the first broad look at
importance of technology-based industries in the state.
<p>
