<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-FBN-LADBROKES'S-ODDS-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; LADBROKES MAKES PACKERS 1 TO 8 FAVORITES TO WIN SUPER BOWL &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Dan Bollerman &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   London, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- British bookmaker Ladbrokes has
made the Green Bay Packers a 1 to 8 favorite to beat the New
England Patriots in the Super Bowl.
<p>
   Ladbrokes is offering 9 to 2 odds on the Patriots winning
Sunday's game at the Louisiana Superdome in New Orleans.
<p>
   With those odds, people who place winning bets on the Packers
would have to wager $8 to win $1. People who place winning bets on
the Patriots would win $9 for every $2 bet.
<p>
   These odds are final, barring any last-minute injuries, said
Ladbrokes's deputy chief oddsmaker Edward Nicholson.
<p>
   The over-under for the game is 49 1/2, with Ladbrokes setting
odds of 10 to 11 that the total number of points scored by both
teams will either exceed or fall short of 49 1/2.
<p>
   About 100 side bets are being offered on the game, including who
will score the first touchdown. Green Bay running back Dorsey
Levens is getting odds of 5 to 1 of scoring first, while Packers'
quarterback Brett Favre is 33 to 1 and New England wide receiver
Troy Brown is 66 to 1.
</TEXT>
