<SLUG> BC-BBN-EXPOS-MOVES-BLOOM </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0341 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-BBN-EXPOS-MOVES-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; MONTREAL EXPOS INVITE 12 NON-ROSTER PLAYERS TO SPRING TRAINING &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Bob Bensch &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Montreal, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- The Montreal Expos invited 12
non-roster players to spring training, several with major league
experience.
<p>
   Receiving invitations were pitchers John DeSilva, Anthony
Telford, Mike Milchin and Carlos Pulido; catchers Michael Barret
and Joe Siddall; infielders Torey Lovullo, Geronimo Pena, Rick Schu
and Andy Stankiewicz and outfielders Milt Cuyler and Steve Pegues.
<p>
   DeSilva, 29, spent last season with the Boston Red Sox' Triple-A
team at Pawtucket and went 4-3 with a 5.21 ERA in 16 starts.
Telford, 30, was 7-2 with a 4.11 ERA in 30 games with Montreal's
Triple-A team at Ottawa. Both are right-handers.
<p>
   Milchin, 28, was 3-1 with a 7.44 ERA in 39 games with the
Minnesota Twins and Baltimore Orioles last season, while Pulido,
25, was 2-8 with a 5.31 ERA with the Chicago Cubs Triple-A team at
Iowa. Both are left-handers.
<p>
   Barrett, 20, was the Expos' first-round pick in 1995 and hit
.238 with Single-A Delmarva last season. Skiddall, 29, hit .280
with Triple-A Charlotte.
<p>
   Lovullo, 31, hit .220 with three home runs and nine runs batted
in over 65 games with the Oakland Athletics last season. He has
spent parts of six major league seasons with the Detroit Tigers,
New York Yankees, California Angels, Seattle Mariners and Oakland.
<p>
   Pena, 29, finished the 1996 season with the Cleveland Indians.
He has a .262 career average in seven major league seasons.
<p>
   Schu, 35, appeared in one game with the Expos last season and
hit .271 with 12 HR and 54 RBI at Ottawa. He has played parts of
nine big league seasons with the Philadelphia Phillies, Baltimore,
Detroit and California.
<p>
   Stankiewicz, 32, hit .286 as a reserve outfielder with Montreal
last season, while Cuyler, 28, hit .200 in 50 games with Boston.
Pegues, 28, hit .341 with the Atlanta Braves' Triple-A team at
Richmond last season.
</TEXT>
