<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-FBN-CARDINALS-JAMIESON-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; ARIZONA CARDINALS NAME DICK JAMIESON OFFENSIVE COORDINATOR &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Erik Matuszewski &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Tempe, Arizona, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- The Arizona Cardinals
named former assistant Dick Jamieson offensive coordinator,
replacing Jim Fassel.
<p>
   Fassel was named head coach of the New York Giants on Jan. 15.
<p>
   Jamieson, who spent the past two seasons as running backs coach
for the Philadelphia Eagles, was an assistant with the Cardinals
from 1980-85.
<p>
   He saw his first tour of duty with the Cardinals on former head
coach Jim Hanifan's staff in 1980 as running backs coach, then was
elevated to offensive coordinator in 1985.
<p>
   After six seasons with the Cardinals, Jamieson spent the next
two campaigns as running backs coach with the Houston Oilers
(1986-87). He then served as assistant head coach and offensive
coordinator at Northwestern University (1990-91), and as running
backs coach at Rutgers University (1992-94) before his two seasons
in Philadelphia.
<p>
   Jamieson first crossed coaching paths with current Cardinals
head coach Vince Tobin while on the University of Missouri's staff
from 1972-77. Jamieson was the school's offensive coordinator while
Tobin served as defensive coordinator.
<p>
   After leaving Missouri, Jamieson had an 11-11 record as the head
coach at Indiana State from 1978-79.
</TEXT>
