 &UR; BC-BBA-RANGERS-HEMOND-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; TEXAS RANGERS SIGN HEMOND, LOMON TO MINOR LEAGUE CONTRACTS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Steve Capo &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Arlington, Texas, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- The Texas Rangers
signed catcher Scott Hemond and pitcher Kevin Lomon to minor league
contracts.
<p>
   Hemond, who was invited to spring training as a non-roster
player, has a .217 career average with 12 homers and 58 runs batted
in during seven major league seasons with the Oakland Athletics,
the Chicago White Sox and St. Louis Cardinals.
<p>
   The 31-year-old Hemond has also played in the outfield and at
all four infield positions during his career. He played last season
at the Cardinals' Triple-A affiliate in Louisville, batting .260
with three homers and 15 RBI in 50 games.
<p>
   Lomon, 25, pitched six games in relief for the Atlanta Braves in
September after going 9-8 with a 4.33 earned run average at
Triple-A Richmond. He had a 4.91 ERA with Atlanta.
<p>
   Lomon made his major league debut in 1995 when he was on the New
York Mets opening day roster and went 0-1 with a 6.75 ERA in six
relief appearances.
</TEXT>
