 &UR; ORLANDO MAGIC ACTIVATE EVANS, PLACE MCCASKILL ON INJURED LIST &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Steve Capo &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Orlando, Florida, Jan. 22 (Bloomberg) -- The Orlando Magic
activated rookie forward Brian Evans, who hasn't played this season
after dislocating his right shoulder during the summer.
<p>
   Evans, Orlando's first-round pick out of Indiana last year,
suffered the injury on July 11 in a practice before summer
professional league play. He underwent surgery July 24 and was
placed on the injured list Oct. 31.
<p>
   To make room on the roster, the Magic placed rookie forward Amal
McCaskill on the injured list with a right calf bruise.
<p>
   McCaskill, taken in the second round by the Magic in 1996, has
averaged 1.7 points and 1.5 rebounds in 11 games this season. He
began the year on the injured list with patella tendinitis and was
activated on Nov. 19.
</TEXT>
