<p>
 &LR; GLOW -- University of California, which makes more money off its
inventions than any other U.S. educational center, has added
another patent to its arsenal: Last month it won a license for
genetically engineering the enzyme that makes fireflies glow. By
Peter Sinton &HT;    
LEVIS -- Levi Strauss &AMP; Co. is seeking a buyer for its Brittania
line of apparel, a brand that has never regained the luster it
achieved among jeans-wearing teen-age girls during the 1970s. By
Carol Emert &HT;    
