<TEXT>
<p>
   PELOSI (Washington) - Just hours after completing a six-year
term on the House ethics committee, San Francisco Congresswoman
Nancy Pelosi provides an inside look at the investigation into
House Speaker Newt Gingrich  &MD;  an inquiry so secret she once had to
ask her husband to leave the bedroom at 3 a.m. as she conducted
business on the phone. In a lengthy interview with the Chronicle,
Pelosi accused GOP leaders of obstructing the ethics process in
order to protect Gingrich, whom she called a ``hypocrite,'' a
``coward,'' deserving of harsher penalties and ethically unfit to
serve as speaker. By Marc Sandalow (Story will move in washington
`w' category)
</TEXT>
