<SLUG> BC-COMPANIES-NYT </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0144 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-COMPANIES-NYT &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (ATTN: Md., Texas, N.J., Canada, Japan, South Africa) &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; COMPANY NEWS &LR;  &QL; 
(th) &QL; 
 &UR; c.1997 N.Y. Times News Service &QC;  &LR;  &QL; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Bridgestone Corp., Tokyo, the automobile tire maker, said it
planned to buy Murray &AMP; Roberts Holdings Ltd.'s Fedstone Ltd. unit
in South Africa for 290 million rand ($62.3 million). Fedstone will
change its name to Bridgestone/Fedstone South Africa.
<p>
   McCormick &AMP; Co., Sparks, Md., said its McCormick Canada Inc.
unit had acquired the Canadian Dry Sauce Mix, Gourmet Collection,
Potato Flavors and Hamburger Fixin's businesses from Reckitt &AMP;
Colman PLC's Reckitt &AMP; Colman Canada Inc. Terms were not disclosed.
<p>
   Union Camp Corp., Wayne, N.J., the paper, packing and chemical
concern, said its Flexible Packaging division will close its plant
in Denton, Texas, on March 28 and lay off about 128 employees.
</TEXT>
