<SLUG> BC-BENPRES-WATER-BID-BLO </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0189 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-BENPRES-WATER-BID-BLOOM &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; BENPRES, LYONNAISE DES EAUX TO RUN HALF OF MANILA WATERWORKS &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service clients) &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; By Alex B. Reyes and Marc R. Crowe &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; c.1997 Bloomberg News &LR;  &QC; 
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   Manila, Jan. 23 (Bloomberg) -- Benpres Holdings Corp. won one of
two contracts to run the Philippines' largest water utility,
extending its dominance of the power and broadcast media into
another industry.
<p>
   The government said Benpres, together with partner Lyonnaise des
Eaux SA of France, won the west half of Metropolitan Waterworks and
Sewerage System. It will run the zone for 25 years.
<p>
   The government also handed the concession for the eastern half
to a group composed of Ayala Corp. and U.S. construction company
Bechtel Group Inc.
<p>
   They beat groups led by Aboitiz Equity Ventures Inc. and Metro
Pacific Corp. in what the International Finance Corp. said is one
of the world's biggest water utility sales.
<p>
   Benpres is the flagship of the influential Lopez family, which
controls the country's biggest power distributor, Manila Electric
Co., and its largest television network, ABS-CBN Broadcasting Corp.
</TEXT>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-22-97 2223EST
</TRAILER>
