<p>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
N.Y. Times Photo Full picture package, moving 1/22/97.
<p>
   NYT Picture clients will automatically receive these photos via
AP's PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on NewsCom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
212-556-4204.
<p>
   (NYT22) UNDATED -- Jan. 22, 1997 -- EXCLUSIVE-SECRET-BENEFACTOR,
1-22 -- Charles Feeney says his money does not drive his life. Over
the last 15 years, the self-made businessman from New Jersey has
given away more than $600 million to hospitals, universities and
other beneficiaries - but has done it in such absolute secrecy that
most recipients never learned who their benefactor was. (Paul
Hosefros/New York Times Photo) *LITE
<p>
   (NYT21) ST. LOUIS -- Jan. 22, 1997 -- ENTERPRISE-RENTACAR-CLR,
1-22 -- Amid a flurry of deals involving its rivals, Enterprise
Rent-a-Car remains in the hands of its founding family. Andrew
Taylor, the chief executive, says he is ``watching the frenzy with
fascination.'' Sticking close to the niche it developed - providing
rentals for customers whose cars are being repaired or who need an
extra car - Enterprise is No. 1 in fleet size and locations. (Peter
Newcomb/New York Times Photo)
<p>
   (NYT20) UNDATED -- Jan. 22, 1997 -- SPAIN-AUTONOMY, 1-22 -- The
city of Elche wants to borrow the Lady of Elche, above, an ancient
stone bust, for an exhibit in this 15th-century castle, below, but
has been rebuffed by Madrid. Elche's request and Madrid's rebuff
are a slice of what is called the ``autonomy question,'' the
growing demand for status and power by the regions of Spain as they
reassert their historical and cultural identity. (Robert Royal/New
York Times Photo)
<p>
   (NYT19) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 22, 1997 -- COHEN-CONFIRM-CLR, 1-22
-- William Cohen is confirmed Wednesday as secretary of defense by
a 99-to-0 vote of the Senate. He is the only Republican in the
Cabinet. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
<p>
   (NYT18) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 22, 1997 -- CUOMO-CONFIRM-CLR, 1-22
-- Andrew Cuomo visits Capitol Hill on Wednesday as the Senate
Banking Committee opens hearings on his nomination as housing
secretary. Cuomo says that if confirmed, one of his first moves
will be to reorganize the management and the direction of the huge
agency. ``We must remain committed to our worthwhile goals, but not
to failed means,'' he says. ``We must be willing to admit that some
programs don't work.'' (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
<p>
   (NYT17) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 22, 1997 -- DALEY-CONFIRM-CLR, 1-22
-- William Daley answers questions Wednesday at his confirmation
hearing for commerce secretary. His wife and daughters look on.
(Vincent J. Ricardel/New York Times Photo)
<p>
   (NYT16) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 22, 1997 -- ABORTION-MARCH-CLR, 1-22
-- On the 24th anniversary of the Supreme Court's decision in Roe
vs. Wade, Hillary Rodham Clinton tells the National Abortion and
Reproductive Rights Action League on Wednesday that guaranteeing
abortion rights is a priority for the Clinton administration. At
the same time, police officers in riot gear turn out in force
outside the Court, left, in response to thousands of anti-abortion
protesters. (Paul Hosefros/New York Times Photo)
<p>
