<p>
   (NYT13) WASHINGTON -- Jan. 22, 1997 -- ALBRIGHT-CONFIRM-CLR,
1-22 -- Secretary of State Madeleine Albright, expected to be sworn
in by President Clinton on Thursday, has put two longtime hands in
top jobs at the State Department. Thomas Pickering, 65, will become
under secretary for political affairs, the third-ranking job in the
State Department, replacing Peter Tarnoff. Stuart Eizenstat, 54,
