<SLUG> BC-LEVIS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
<DATE> 01-22 </DATE>
<NWORDS> 0434 </NWORDS>
<PREAMBLE>
 &UR; BC-LEVIS-SFCHRON &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; (CORRECTS SPELLING OF BRITTANIA) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; (For use by clients of New York Times News Service) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; Levi's Will Dump Its Brittania Sportswear &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By Carol Emert &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.1997 San Francisco Chronicle &QC;  &LR; 
Levi Strauss &AMP; Co. is seeking a buyer for its Brittania line of
apparel, a brand that has never regained the luster it achieved
among jeans-wearing teen-age girls during the 1970s. &HT;    Citing a decision to concentrate on its core business of more
upscale clothing, San Francisco-based Levi's said it has asked
Morgan Stanley to peddle Brittania Sportswear Ltd., which it
acquired a decade ago.
</PREAMBLE>
<TEXT>
<p>
   ``When (Levi's) bought it, it was a terminal case, and they've
never been able to get it off the ground,'' said Alan Millstein,
president of Fashion Network Report in New York.
<p>
   ``It's not a designer name, it has no sex appeal, and probably
they don't want to put big advertising dollars behind it, which
would be the only way they could sustain it,'' he added.
<p>
   Brittania once was a leading department store brand but now is
sold by mass merchants such as Kmart.
<p>
   Millstein said the brand has faced growing competition in recent
years from low-priced, in-house casual labels such as J.C. Penney's
Arizona and Sears, Roebuck and Co.'s Canyon River Blues.
<p>
   Levi's spokesman Vada Manager said Brittania has been ``a
success'' for the company, though he declined to comment on
Brittania's earnings or profitability.
<p>
   Manager said Levi's decided to sell Brittania so that the
company could focus on its three core brands: Levi's, Dockers and
Slate, a dress pant introduced last year.
<p>
   ``We believe Brittania could be viable as a stand-alone business
and has a future in the mass-market area,'' Manager said. However,
Target stores, one of Brittania's major retailers, has been phasing
out sales of the brand for several months.
<p>
   Another big outlet, Kmart, said it's uncertain whether it will
continue to carry Brittania, its second-largest line of denim
clothing after Wrangler (for men) and Chic (for women).
<p>
   Brittania produces jeans for men and women. It also makes men's
and boys' casual pants and tops, leather accessories, socks, shoes,
underwear, outerwear, watches and fleece.
<p>
   The clothes are sold under the label ``Brittania by Levi's,''
indicating that Levi's attempted to capitalize on the cachet of its
name without selling its core products in discount stores.
<p>
   Brittania was purchased by Levi's in 1987 from Asian Pacific
Industries, which at the time was in Chapter 11 bankruptcy
proceedings.
<p>
   Today, Brittania employs 120 people.
</TEXT>
<TRAILER>
