who is a top bank appointee sought last year to have that
institution provide financing for a store franchise to a woman
whose large donations to the Democratic Party have come under
investigation. By Christopher Drew and Jeff Gerth.
<p>
    &UR; BUSINESS DAY  &MD;  (Moved in ``f'' category)  &LR; 
<p>
   ENTERPRISE-RENTACAR (St. Louis)  &MD;  For 40 years, Enterprise
Rent-a-Car Inc. has gone against all the conventional industry
wisdom. Not only has it ceded the bread-and-butter airport business
to Hertz, Avis and other national competitors, but it has also done
without celebrity-driven advertisements and catchy slogans. Yet
while Hertz Corp. and the others got the higher profiles, the St.
Louis-based Enterprise has become the industry's giant. By Gianna
Jacobson.
<p>
   (ART ADV: Graphic has been sent to NYT graphics clients. Photo
