Upjohn with disdain and apprehension, even before the surprise
resignation this week of John Zabriskie, the American chief
executive of the London-based drug maker. But a few contrarians saw
a brighter side. By Milt Freudenheim.
<p>
   AUTOINSURE-ECONSCENE  &MD;  The proposal from Gov. Christie Whitman
of New Jersey last week to allow motorists to buy no-frill,
no-fault auto insurance that could pare premiums by as much as
one-fourth was a strong endorsement for a fledgling idea that has
been unable to take flight nationally. By Peter Passell.
